         <div type="edition" xml:lang="la" xml:space="preserve"><head xml:lang="en">Text</head><div subtype="fragment" n="a" type="textpart"><ab>
                  <lb n="1"/><persName type="emperor"><name type="praenomen" nymRef="Marcus"><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arco</ex></expan></name> <name type="gentilicium" nymRef="Annius">Annio</name>
                     <lb n="2"/><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Verus">Vero</name> <persName type="emperor"><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Augustus"><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan></name></persName> 
                  <w lemma="filius"><expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan></w></persName>
               </ab></div><div subtype="fragment" n="b" type="textpart"><ab>
                  <lb n="1"/><persName type="emperor"><name type="praenomen" nymRef="Lucius"><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan></name> <name type="gentilicium" nymRef="Aurelius">Aurelio</name>
                  <lb n="2"/><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Commodus">Commodo</name>
                     <lb n="3"/><persName type="emperor"><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Augustus"><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan></name></persName> 
                  <w lemma="filius"><expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan></w></persName>
               </ab></div><div subtype="fragment" n="c" type="textpart"><ab>
                  <lb n="1"/><persName type="emperor"><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Lucilla">Lucillae</name>
                     <lb n="2"/><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Augusta"><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustae</ex></expan></name></persName>
               </ab></div></div>
         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p>a) To Marcus Annius Verus, son of Augustus</p><p>b) To Lucius Aurelius Commodus, son of Augustus </p><p>c) To Lucilla Augusta </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>These are all children of Marcus Aurelius. Lucilla received the title Augusta at her marriage with
               Lucius Verus c.164.
               The panels were presumably cut after that, but before October 166, when M. Annius Verus
               and Commodus received the title Caesar. </p>
         </div>
